## The updated “Pair Candidate Selection” section I would use

Here is the section I would actually put in the plan.

```text
### Pair Candidate Selection

The final model is not a single pair-only head and it is not a legacy
single-placement policy model. It is a pair-action model with auxiliary proposal
views.

The searched action is always an unordered pair after the opening. Candidate
selection uses model-derived proposal functions only to avoid exhaustive pair
enumeration and to improve candidate recall.

#### New Model Outputs Used For Candidate Selection

cell_marginal_logits:
  One logit per full legal row. This is trained from pair posterior marginals
  and terminal cell labels. It is not the final policy.

pair_completion_logits(anchor, candidate):
  Conditional completion score for a second cell given an anchor cell. Because
  the true pair is unordered, this is trained and used symmetrically in both
  orientations.

pair_proposal_score(i, j):
  Cheap symmetric low-rank pair score used for direct top-k pair retrieval.
  This may be computed as a biaffine or dot-product retrieval score over legal
  cell embeddings.

pair_joint_logits(i, j):
  Rich symmetric biaffine pair score over admitted candidate rows. This is the
  main model prior consumed by sampled joint-pair MCTS.

#### Candidate Sources

1. terminal_exact_v1
   Exact win-in-one and lose-in-one protection. Includes immediate winning
   pairs, terminal-equivalent winning pairs, and pairs that block all opponent
   immediate win requirements. These candidates are protected and cannot be
   evicted.

2. direct_pair_retrieval
   Retrieve high-scoring unordered pairs from the cheap symmetric pair proposal
   score. This is the primary model-led source.

3. anchor_conditioned_completion
   Select anchor cells from cell_marginal_logits and/or pair proposal summaries.
   For each anchor, use pair_completion_logits to propose completions. Add both
   unordered orientations or use logsumexp over both orientations.

4. cell_marginal_cross
   Add a capped cross-product of top marginal cells. This source is secondary
   and exists for stability, not as the main policy.

5. structured_diversity
   Add geometry/diversity candidates by legal-row bucket, distance bucket,
   axis/sector, and window participation. This prevents support collapse.

6. blind_canary
   Add a tiny deterministic diagnostic sample to measure candidate blind spots.

#### Final Selection

All candidate pairs are canonicalized, deduplicated, source-merged, and assigned
metadata. Protected terminal candidates are kept first. Remaining slots are
filled by source quotas and pair_joint_logits. No candidate may enter search
without source metadata, proposal metadata, and pair-row identity.

Legal-order first-N pair enumeration is forbidden as normal runtime candidate
selection. It is allowed only as a diagnostic baseline.
